<emphasis bold="true" box="[459,695,1615,1642]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716">Pezotettix giornae</emphasis>
(Rossi, 1794)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1155,1669,1728]" box="[192,1155,1669,1694]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716">
This species is very common in 
<collectingCountry box="[552,599,1669,1694]" name="Italy" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Iorio C &amp; Scherini R &amp; Fontana P &amp; Buzzetti FM &amp; Kleukers R &amp; Massa B" box="[613,791,1669,1694]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716" pagination="579" refId="ref2036" refString="Iorio C, Scherini R, Fontana P, Buzzetti FM, Kleukers R, Massa B. 2019. Grassophers &amp; Crikets of Italy. A photoghraphic field guide to all the species. Verona: WBA Handbooks 10; p. 579." type="journal article" year="2019">Iorio et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). It is generally observable from
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1717" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1155,1669,1728]" lastBlockId="5.[160,1155,867,996]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1717" pageId="4" pageNumber="1716">
June to October, overwintering as adults. It is present in the southern part of the country and on the islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Fontana P &amp; Buzzetti FM &amp; Cogo A &amp; Ode B" box="[378,593,867,892]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1717" pagination="592" refId="ref1892" refString="Fontana P, Buzzetti FM, Cogo A, Ode B. 2002. Guida al riconoscimento e allo studio di cavallette, grilli, mantidi e insetti affini del Veneto. Vicenza: Guide Natura / 1 Museo Naturalistico Archeologico; p. 592." type="book chapter" year="2002">Fontana et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Massa B &amp; Fontana P &amp; Buzzetti FM &amp; Kleukers R &amp; Ode B" box="[605,795,867,892]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1717" refId="ref2293" refString="Massa B, Fontana P, Buzzetti FM, Kleukers R, Ode B. 2012. Orthoptera. Fauna d'Italia, XLVIII. Bologna: Calderini; p. 563." type="journal volume" year="2012">Massa et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Iorio C &amp; Scherini R &amp; Fontana P &amp; Buzzetti FM &amp; Kleukers R &amp; Massa B" box="[806,979,867,892]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1717" pagination="579" refId="ref2036" refString="Iorio C, Scherini R, Fontana P, Buzzetti FM, Kleukers R, Massa B. 2019. Grassophers &amp; Crikets of Italy. A photoghraphic field guide to all the species. Verona: WBA Handbooks 10; p. 579." type="journal article" year="2019">Iorio et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, the observations made in this study represent interesting data for the Alpine region. During monitoring in 2019, paired individuals were observed on three occasions (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1142,936,961]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="6.[160,225,834,857]" captionTargetBox="[162,1152,142,802]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[162,1152,142,802]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 6. Mating of Pezotettix giornae (9 February 2019)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757229/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1717">Figure 6</figureCitation>
). Plots in which it is present: T1 and T2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
